Global Antithrombotic Drugs Market Insights
Antithrombotic Drugs Market size was valued at USD 25.4 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 37.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.8% from 2024 to 2030.

Antithrombotic Drugs Market Overview
The global antithrombotic drugs market was valued at approximately USD 38.5 billion in 2023 and is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 5.2% from 2024 to 2030. The market's growth is primarily driven by the increasing prevalence of cardiovascular diseases (CVDs), rising demand for preventive therapies, and advancements in drug formulations. As the aging population grows globally, the need for anticoagulation therapy is expanding, creating new opportunities for the market. Additionally, ongoing innovations in drug development and increasing awareness about the importance of managing thrombotic disorders are expected to further propel market growth.

